cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper combines game theory and information theory to study the interference channel, which is a communication scenario. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses game theory to define a Nash equilibrium region, making cs.GT (Game Theory) another likely sub-category. The interference channel is a networked system, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions optimization, which could fall under cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization) or cs.SI (Systems and Control).
